.TH BUGFIX-BRANCH 1 "November 2023" "3.0" "Automation Manual"

.SH NAME
bugfix-branch \- create a new bug fix branch

.SH SYNOPSIS
bugfix-branch [-r] [-o <owner>] [-b <base-branch>] <repository> <branch-name>

bugfix-branch -h

.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a new Git bug fix branch in the given repository and publishes it to GitHub.

If the VS Code command: `code` is available, the project will be opened in VS Code.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
-r
Reuse the current VS Code window.

.TP
-o <owner>
Owner of the repository. Defaults to "SituDevelopment".

.TP
-b <base-branch>
Name of the branch from which to take the bug fix branch. Defaults to the repository's default branch.

.TP
<repository>
Name of the repository.

.TP
<branch-name>
Name of the bug fix branch to create. This name will be prefixed with `bug/`.

.TP
-h
Display help and exit.

.SH AUTHOR
William Sawyer (william@situ.com.au)
